Class EditGardenView

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.Parent
javafx.scene.layout.Region
javafx.scene.layout.Pane
javafx.scene.layout.BorderPane
pkgView.EditGardenView
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class EditGardenView
extends javafx.scene.layout.BorderPane
Author:
Ryan Dean The EditGardenView class extends BorderPane, and is the implementation for the "Edit Garden" screen of the program. This screen is where users drag and drop plant objects onto their previously drawn garden plot.

  • Constructor Details

    • EditGardenView

      public EditGardenView​(View view, java.lang.String loadName)
      Constructor initializes this view class. Takes in plant and plot data from the controller to build garden shown in the scene. Instantiates and fills the DragDropCarouselView with plant objects.
      Parameters:
      view - The program's View that is only initialized once.
      loadName - The user-input name of the garden being loaded. Null if a new garden is being made.

  • Method Details

    • makeCanvas

      public void makeCanvas​(java.util.HashMap<Soil,​java.util.Stack<java.util.ArrayList<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Double>>> plots)
      Method for re-drawing the garden plots input in Draw Garden onto this class's canvas.
      Parameters:
      plots - A hashmap holding the list of points of each plot drawn in Draw Garden, organized by soil type.

    • updateInfoPanel

      public void updateInfoPanel​(int dollars, int leps, java.util.ArrayList<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer>> sortedLeps)
      Method for updating the values in the budget, lep number, and lep species display. Called whenever a plan object is added or removed from the garden. Also makes a button that opens a pop-up window containing a full list of lep species supported.
      Parameters:
      dollars - Current total cost of all plants in garden
      leps - Current number of leps supported by plants in garden
      sortedLeps - List of the lep species supported by the plants in the garden and number of plants that support them

    • openLepPopup

      public void openLepPopup​(java.util.ArrayList<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer>> sortedLeps)
      Method called by the "See more" button in the lep species display. Opens a pop-up listing all lep species supported.
      Parameters:
      sortedLeps - List of all lep species supported by plants in garden, sorted by number of plants supporting them

    • makePlantView

      public PlantView makePlantView​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> name_soil_info, int spread)
      Method for making PlantView objects, setting appropriate handlers and tooltips. Used for plants initially added to the carousel.
      Parameters:
      name_soil_info - List holding plant info put into tooltips
      spread - Integer for plant spread diameter
      Returns:
      PlantView object ready to be placed in DragDropCarousel

    • replacePlant

      public void replacePlant​(int index)
      Method that duplicates plants dragged out of carousel, and puts them in place of the removed plant.
      Parameters:
      index - Integer representing the position of the plant to duplicate in the carousel's plant list.

    • drawSpread

      public void drawSpread​(int index, double x, double y)
      Method that draws a Circle (if spread large enough to display) or rectangle (if not), visually representing plant spread. These shapes are added to garden, continually updated to location of their associated plant.
      Parameters:
      index - Index of the plant in this class's plant list that the spread object is supposed to represent.
      x - Double representing x-location of the plant this spread is associated with.
      y - Double representing y-location of the plant this spread is associated with.

    • computeScaleSize

      public double computeScaleSize​(PlantView plant)
      Helper method used by DrawSpread to calculate the radius of the spread object according to scale factor.
      Parameters:
      plant - Plant whose spread should be altered by scale factor.
      Returns:
      Double representing the spread of the plant according to the scale factor of the garden.

    • updateSpread

      public void updateSpread​(int index, boolean inGarden, boolean overlap)
      Method called whenever plant is dragged to change color of its associated spread object according to plot conditions. Blue: accepted. Yellow: overlaps another spread. Red: outside valid soil type.
      Parameters:
      index - Index of spread to be changed in this class's plantSpreads.
      inGarden - Boolean representing whether the base of the plant is in its correct soil type, computed by model.
      overlap - Boolean representing whether plant's spread overlaps another's, computed by model.

    • addPlantFromCarousel

      public void addPlantFromCarousel​(int index, javafx.scene.Node n)
      Method facilitating transport of PlantView Node from DragDropCarousel to this class's garden stackpane.
      Parameters:
      index - Index of the plant in the carousel's plants list.
      n - PlantView node being dragged.
